  "text": "ΔN, ΔO, and ΔE can be calculated as follows (DiPrete et al. 1922 [CITATION_1] where P g (k) (P g (k′) ) is the distribution across the educational categories in country k (k′), p g (k) is the share of people of country k who are in the educational program g, and p j|k is the likelihood of being in occupational category j, given one's educational program is g. See DiPrete et al. (2017) for further details.",
